{
  "texts": [
    "Indeed, we see that empty spots tend to be smaller with lower average/maximum weight (Supplementary Fig. 2c and d).",
    "On a small fraction of spots from all fields of view, we train a random forest classifier (scikit-learn v1.1.3) with area, maximum and average weights as features to predict empty/nonempty labels (Supplementary Fig. 2e).",
    "We applied the classifier to all spots and obtained emptiness probabilities and set a threshold on these probabilities (0.3-0.35).",
    "Spot assignment to cells.",
    "The cell boundaries were computed by applying find_boundaries (scikit-image 0.19.3 91) to the segmentation mask."
  ]
}